HEADWORD: Tenderfoot
<hw>Ten"der*foot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
delicate person; one not inured to the hardship and rudeness of pioneer
life.</def> <mark>[Slang, Western U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Boy scout</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tender-hearted</ent>⟦br⟧
